      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the mixed legacy thing, but u said it was a \"strategic success\" because gaddafi was toppled. but if the result was just a power vacuum and civil war, doesn't that mean the strategy itself was fundamentally flawed from the start? like, if u know nation-building is hard, was it even a \"success\" to remove the one thing keeping it stable?",
